race.comment: FIORSUM FRED (1) resumed in good order at Newcastle, beaten 1.7L over 1400m. He'd come off a trial win here and has more up his sleeve. Maps for a soft run and Bullock is a key jockey engagement. TAIPAN LEGEND (2) was quickly back to form, leading and winning an 84 by 3L over a mile. Led and won a 66 at the track the last time he tackled this distance and he draws an inside gate. He's further improved and Heywood replaces Weir in the saddle. She rides PENSATIVA (8), who peaks and has been within range in Highway grade at Rosehill her last two. Jumped from cruel barriers in both and she finally draws an inside barrier. Gets her chance in this company. SPEEDY HENRY (10) will find this easier than Rosehill and tackles a mile for the first time. He's going well enough to consider.
